The OnTimer() Function in the Strategy Tester 
#


MQL5 provides the opportunity for handling timer events. The call of the 
OnTimer()
 handler is done regardless of the test mode. This means that if a test is running in the "Opening prices only" mode for the period H4, and the EA has a timer set to a call per second, then at the opening of each H4 bar, the OnTick() handler will be called one time, and the OnTimer() handler will be called 14400 times (3600 seconds * 4 hours ). The amount by which the testing time of the EA will be increased depends on the logic of the EA.


